.so fork.tmac
.SS GET_TERMCAP_BY_CODE
.PP
This function returns a control string for a given two-character
capcode.
.IP
.ct_get_termcap_by_code
.TP
.I value
is a pointer to a pointer to which the termcap value, if found, will
be returned.
.TP
.I capcode
is a two-character code for which to search.
.TP
.B RETURN VALUE
is
.B true
if found or
.B false
if not found.
.PP
Following the convention established by the
.B less
command, it first checks the environment for overrides defined
with a variable name derived from a prefix of
.B LESS_TERMCAP_
followed by the two-character code.
If there is no LESS_TERMCAP_ environment variable, it will return
the associated termcap string from the terminfo database (see
.BR terminfo (5)).
.PP
If an application prefers not to leave the definition to the user,
convert the capcode to a capname using the
.B capname_from_code
function, then using
.BR get_termcap_by_name :
.IP
.EX
const char *capval;
if (get_termcap_by_name(&capval, capname_from_code(code)))
   do_something(capval);
.EE




